Territory of Washington, Plaintiff vs. Ray Raymond, Defendant} In the District Court of the Territory of Washington, and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, holding terms at Cheney Spokane Falls, Spokane County, in said Territory.

To the Sheriff Spokane County, Greeting: In the Name of the United States, You are hereby commanded to summon Alexander Bustord and J.M. Masonourth to be and appear before the District Court at the Court House, in Cheney Spokane Falls, in said County, on the forthwith day of December A.D. 1886, at o'clock M. to there give evidence in the above entitled cause on the part of said Territory.
WITESS the Hon. George Turner, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the Seal thereof affixed, this 9th day of Dec. A.D. 1886
